com.ibm.team.build.client
Interface ITeamBuildBaseClient

All Known Subinterfaces:
ITeamBuildClient, ITeamBuildRequestClient
public interface ITeamBuildBaseClient

Base interface for all team build client library interfaces. It provides support for common functionality that can be executed through any of the team build client libraries.

Since:
0.6

save

IBuildDefinition save(IBuildDefinition buildDefinition,
                      org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor progressMonitor)
                      throws TeamRepositoryException,
                             TeamBuildDuplicateItemException,
                             java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
Save the given build definition to the repository. If the build definition is new, the IBuildAverageDataitem will also be created and assigned to the build definition.

Parameters:
buildDefinition - The build definition to save. Must be a working copy.
progressMonitor - The progress monitor to track progress on or null if progress monitoring is not desired.
Returns:
The new state of the build definition.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the buildDefinition is null.
TeamRepositoryException - If an error occurs while accessing the repository.
TeamBuildDuplicateItemException - If a build definition with the id of the definition being saved already exists.

delete

void delete(IBuildDefinitionHandle buildDefinitionHandle,
            org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor progressMonitor)
            throws TeamRepositoryException,
                   TeamBuildStateException,
                   java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
Deletes the specified build definition from the repository. The build definition is permanently removed from the repository. The build definition can not be deleted if there are any build results associated with it in the repository. The build results must be deleted first.

Parameters:
buildDefinitionHandle - The handle to the build definition to delete.
progressMonitor - The progress monitor to track progress on or null if progress monitoring is not desired.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the buildDefinition is null.
TeamRepositoryException - If an error occurs while deleting the item from the repository.
TeamBuildStateException - If the repository contains any build results that are associated with the build definition being deleted.
